# 📈 Exchange Rate Forecasting using Time Series Analysis

## 📌 Objective  
Forecast future exchange rates using **ARIMA** and **Exponential Smoothing** based on historical data.

## 📊 Dataset  
- **Dataset:** Exchange Rate Dataset  
- **File:** `exchange_rate.csv`  
- **Features:**  
   - Date  
   - Exchange rate 

## 🧠 Techniques Used  
- **Data Preprocessing:**  
   - Loaded and parsed date column  
   - Handled missing values and anomalies  

- **Time Series Analysis:**  
   - Visualized trends and seasonality  
   - Analyzed autocorrelation using ACF & PACF plots  

- **Modeling Approaches:**  
   - **ARIMA:** Parameter tuning, model fitting, residual diagnostics, forecasting  
   - **Exponential Smoothing:** Selected appropriate smoothing model, optimized parameters, and forecasted values  

- **Evaluation Metrics:**  
   - Mean Absolute Error (MAE)  
   - Root Mean Square Error (RMSE)  
   - Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE)  

## 🔍 Analysis and Interpretation  
- **Model Comparison:** Compared ARIMA and Exponential Smoothing for accuracy and efficiency  
- **Insights:** Identified trends and optimal forecasting techniques  

## 🚀 Results  
- **Best Model:** Determined based on lowest error metrics  
- **Forecasting Accuracy:** Achieved reliable future exchange rate predictions  


